en_565756_0	Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi on Thursday (9) presided a security coordinating conference with representatives of all state, semi-state and private sector institutes in the Kilinochchi district in order to explain prevailing security concerns and security arrangements kept in place by the Security Forces to stem extremist activities, aimed at bringing normalcy to the area.
en_565756_1	It took place at the conference hall of the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi.
en_565756_2	A total of 39 officials participated in the interactive meeting and highlighted difficulties faced by their workers and customers due to prevailing circumstances.
en_565756_3	The Kilinochchi Commander further explained about the efforts made by the Security Forces to enhance security in the area and urged all participants to extend their fullest support to the Security Forces.
en_565756_4	General Officer Commanding 57 Division, Brigadier A.S Hewawitharana and several senior officers also contributed to the conference.
